Heat olive oil in stock pot over medium high heat. Add chopped onion, celery, and carrots and cook until they begin to to soften slightly. Add vegetable stock and ham bone. Bring to boil and reduce heat; simmer for an hour. Remove ham bone from pot and pick off ham; return meat to pot. Add the beans. Add package of Idahoan Roasted Garlic Flavored Mashed Potatoes and stir thoroughly. Mix in chopped parsley and adjust seasoning if necessary. Cook for an additional 5 minutes and serve.